  "title" : "Stop ConcurrentTaskScheduler when spring context closed",
  "body" : "<p>I am writing a simple spring application with <code>AnnotationConfigApplicationContext</code>. I have a <code>ConcurrentTaskScheduler</code> in my application. What is the best practice for stopping the <code>ConcurrentTaskScheduler</code> when the spring context closed?</p>\n\n<p>Update: The main problem is when Junit close the context in @After annotation all threads will be terminated but when i manually close the context at the end of application, Some threads running by <code>ConcurrentTaskScheduler</code> will continue running.</p>\n"
